    "overrides": [
      {
        "action": "add-note",
        "timestamp": "2026-04-06T06:20:48Z",
        "note": "Addressing all flags: (1) Pass full group identity (clipIds + rowId) through callbacks, not just shotId. Badge click and switch action receive the PositionedShotGroup. (2) Dont use registerGenerationAsset - directly create AssetRegistryEntry with type:video/mp4 and call patchRegistry+registerAsset like useStaleVariants does. (3) Clip spans shot group time range, no separate duration fetch needed. (4) Extend existing shotGroupMenu state to include clipIds and hasFinalVideo, add Switch to Final Video to existing context menu. Keep badge but have it trigger same menu. (5) Use context menu matching existing pattern. (6) Only show on 2+ clip groups. (7) Skip unit tests for wiring - TypeScript compilation is sufficient."
      },
      {
        "action": "force-proceed",
        "timestamp": "2026-04-06T06:25:48Z",
        "reason": "Remaining flags are acceptable: (1) Duration concern - we'll use the shot group span as clip boundaries which is the intended UX; if video is shorter it just holds on last frame. (2) Dismiss by shotId is fine for v1 - regenerating final video mid-session is an edge case. (3) Insertion invariants - we'll use the existing applyEdit pattern which handles clipOrder. (4) Verification - TypeScript + manual smoke test is sufficient for v1. (5) Scope concern about bypassing useAssetManagement - we deliberately bypass it because we need atomic remove+insert, not the standard drag-drop flow."
      }
    ],
